caption: My top scene for tasty italian food. Nice place to think about business. The service was very helpful and welcoming. Bring your hunger - portions are filling. This place has many reviews for a reason.
Good spot for tasty italian food. looking forward to going back again. this place has a nice design.
Italian food... so tasty. Got there about two, it was not packed. Looking forward to returning with my relatives. This place has a nice feel to it.

We ate here at a classic Italian Dinner time (1:30pm, Sunday) and it was a very enjoyable meal. The food was very fresh, from the eggplant to the beet ravioli and grilled octopus and the “piattini” menu permitted a sampling of lots of items (think tapas). The service was attentive and we added a bottle of Chianti to round out a wonderful meal. Reasonably priced for this level of quality and we all highly recommend!
I love this place to death. They have great food , esp for the gluten free folks(also veggie friendly!!) they do a wonderful dinner theater. Easily one of my favorite places in Baltimore
Great live jazz and great food.
Like Mamma is in the kitchen.
Decent food. Live music. The staff can be dense depending on who you get. Pretty decent experience.

Placed our order ... waited an hour and 15 minutes... we were told food would be another 15. We had a show we needed to get to so we just told them to box the food. Another fifteen minutes passed without any food so we just asked to cancel the order and we’d pay for the wine we drank. They told us to wait because “it was being boxed right now”. We waited another five minutes before realizing they hadn’t even put the order in. They’d been lying to us all night. Then they had the audacity to ask us to pay for the food we hadn’t received “because they’d have to throw it away”. We got no discount and no service at all. I can understand delays but not getting lied to like that. Our experience was shared by most of the restaurant that night too.
Good food. Service was friendly but slow. Make sure you order the grilled artichokes...so good.
Wonderful staff and good food
Hidden gem in Little Italy. Sunday night Jazz sesh is awesome. Came in for desert and digestif and stayed for the people and the music. Get the Cheesecake!!!!!!

Good food and amazing live music
Most interesting food ever.
The food was great and the atmosphere was wonderful
That food is alright, but the cabaret show was top notch. A very enjoyable evening in little Italy.
Always a lovely meal and with live music most nights.

Nice Italian joint in Little Italy.  Ate upstairs while watching a jazz band.  Food was ok which is why only 4 stars.  Friendly staff.  Place was clean.  Only downside is safety after dark in the area.

Delicious food in a wonderful old town Baltimore atmosphere.  Amazingly reasonable prices for authentic Italian food.  We loved the Beet Ravioli in Mushroom Ragu.  Excellent wine list, fabulous service! We will go back soon!
The food is excellent and the staff is delightful.

I really appreciated that everything was clearly labeled vegetarian/vegan. I had the beet ravioli, which was delicious, as well as the tiramisu (which was a little too alcoholic for my liking). My friend had Gorgonzola gnocchi which he didn't like as much.
Nice place

Very disappointing! The boss and I randomly stopped in for a quick meal before a recent show at the MECU Pavillion. The beer was warm and the lasagna was cold, sauce was watery and not much taste . Service was ok, but you would think that ANY restaurant that is located in Little Italy would provide a better meal than the one we were served. Won't be going there again.
Im impressed that artists get sponsors.   They deserve it SMS the art is beyond belief.   I would have liked to have seen more 3D.

Our server Ignosio was woderful, professional and attentive to our dining needs. Cheesecake was scrumptious!! We will return, thanks for a memorable experience Germano's.

I absolutely loved the jam session we just so happen to walk up on. Can't wait to get back to the sessions

A small eatery in Little Italy.  Staff is attentive, dining room decoration is nice.  I had the Spaghetti with Two Cheeses and Pepper (Spaghetti Cacio e Pepe) which was made with good quality pasta, and the description is exactly what I got.  Nothing fancy, and I liked it.  The wife had Lasagna (Lasagna Classica); she was not as satisfied with her meal, commenting that her Lasagna was much better.  Her verdict was the meat was not fresh, and there was no Ricotta in the dish.

Food was tasty ! Service was good. Some people feel little 🇮🇹 is over priced.

Wonderful homemade heartfelt Italian cuisine. The inventive beet ravioli and grilled artichokes were the show stealers! The fresh brussel sprouts and the polpettes were nothing to scoff at, either. The cheesecake at the end? Perfection. What a happy night!
Nice atmosphere. 7 minute walk from inner harbor. Service very friendly. Food was good.

Delightful in every way. The vegan menu is a hit. And the grilled octopus is perfection.

I love spicy food but my bowl of food was just a plate of fire. I also ordered the apple fritters for dessert and it was so incredibly mediocre. We really wanted to love this place for the vegan menu but the food was mediocre. All three adults in my party agreed. As a longtime vegan I've had plenty of stellar meals at many restaurants. We all tried different menu items, including an appetizer, and tasted each other's meals to sample. It was decent but not somewhere any of us would return. I can cook much better at home.

Great spot in little Italy. Good food, good wine selection and friendly and knowledgeable staff. Order the olives they're amazing! Within walking distance of Vaccaro's for cappuccino and canoli afterwards.

Quickly became our new favorite! Delicious and authentic Italian dinner, friendly service and a warm atmosphere. The Brussel sprouts and shrimp were delicious. Everyone loved the lasagna and we finished everything off with some of the best cheesecake! We left full and happy, and will be back for more.

We attended Bottomless Brunch to support a great band, the Foggy Bottom Womp Stompers, and unfortunately, that's the only recommendation I can approve. Check them out, but avoid brunch.  1 hour and 15 minutes from order till getting our food.  $15 tickets for the show, and an unannounced, mandatory "Bottomless Brunch" (all you can eat) for $25, but all mimosas and bloody mary's are an additional purchase.  We order a second course of food, that arrived literally as the show ended.  This said... the French Toast was sublime, the gnocchi melted in your mouth and the egg is skillet was awful.  Two of us ordered bloody mary's and both were undrinkable.  The MC performed a series of disturbing magic tricks in the middle of the show.  The dancers who were great, but everything else going on around them made it too painful to enjoy.
Authentic northern Italian food
Great service and great food
Excellent service, beautiful atmosphere
The food here was out of this world good and the staff was extremely hospitable. Put this on your list of places you must eat.
Food was excellent and the featured artist Marcus Dagan was terrific on the piano.

Stopped in for dinner with about 6 colleagues after a seminar at the Convention Center.  If I had to describe this place using only one word, it would be "WOW"!!!! We were greeted by the owner, who came out to show us an amazing painting of Nancy Pelosi and her family and tell us a little story.  We felt welcome right away.  The food was as close to perfect as it gets... the Porchetta was moist and seasoned just the way I like it... and even though they didn't have a regular house salad on the menu, the chef happily made one for me upon my request.  DO YOURSELF A FAVOR AND VISIT THIS QUAINT LITTLE PLACE IF YOU'RE EVER IN THE BALTIMORE AREA!!!

The only reason this place doesnt get one star is for the amazing cheesecake.  Everything else is ok but too expensive. Lousy service waited an hour before ordering.  I will come back for the cheesecake though.
Nice Italian Restaurant in Baltimore!!

The music with dinner was fantastic! The decor is very nice, the setting was quite lovely, except the ceiling tiles; a little dingy looking (ceiling tiles need to be replaced immediately), but nicely themed; painted, etc... Our waitress was melancholy, stressed and seemingly overworked with all the tables she had at once. At times, we ran out of ice tea, and waited a while for appetizers and food, but the service was not terrible (I tipped 20%). The appetizers (brussels sprouts) wwere very good. However, the rest of dinner was terrible at best. Our party of three tried the bread, cheese pizza, and lasagna and they were all terrible (flavor). The sauce on the lasagna tasted like a mixture of Ragu spaghetti sauce and carryout ketchup! The pizza was soggy, and the bread was hard as a rock, with no flavor at all (the second batch brought out was a little warmer and softer but still tasteless. Not what you expect from a italian restaurant). My wifes work colleague made us lasagna the other day that was far better in every aspect (taste, viscosity, warmth, presentation, spices, preparation,  etc...) HOWEVER... The live music (The Carl Grubbs Quartet) was simply amazing! Germano's Piattini supports live music from different local bands to play while having dinner. Because of this, even though the food was not good at all (except the brussel sprouts (me), and the cheesecake according to my wife) I will happily eat their again (music nights only). They must make some dishes that are good, right? I will exhaust them all for good obvionce, and live jazz music, which this place has!
The service and food were not what was expected for the price you pay. The main meal was incredibly greasy and tasted as if it came out of a box.
Great music! The food was so-so.
My favorite Italian restaurant in Baltimore! We drive up from DC just to eat their lasagna and gnocchi - highly recommend making this spot your regular place to eat.
Always a perfect meal, greeted with a smile every time. Gnocchi is to die for (and so if the lasagna)!
Great place with good food and different seating options where you can have a quiet dinner downstairs or good live entertainment upstairs.
I love this place. It's the best Italian food I've had since I left New York. Definitely try the Brussels sprouts, too. So good.
My kids brought me here for dinner—it was so delicious.  Really authentic home cooked lasagna—and all the staff are so nice.  I can’t wait to go back!
This place was hit or miss but the hits where exceptional.
Food was good but service was really slow. And they weren't busy.
Best restaurant in little italy. Melt in your mouth homemade gnocchi you must try!

Just has lunch at Germano’s Piattini in Little Italy.   The food Is fabulous - I had the homemade pasta -Tagliatella Alla Bolognese, and had their homemade cheese cake which was out of this word.    I also visited Germano’s Cabaret a couple weeks ago for dinner and a show.  What a great time.  The lamb chop dinner was also absolutely delicious.  The show was equally great.  If you are looking for a night out in Baltimore I highly recommend you go to Germano’s.   The owner Germano is a wonderful person. This place is very special.
I was very disappointed with this restaurant. The waiter was very slow and the food was nothing out of the ordinary.  There are much better choices in Little Italy.

Nice service and good looking dishes, altho i was stomach sick that day so i unfortunately didnt get to try the pasta... i had some warm bread (comes with oil and balsamic vinegar) and then had the soup of the day, which was very tasty and warming.
Great Beet Ravioli dish! The Veal Marsala was very tasty.  But the cheesecake with lemon confit and caramel was awesome!

Absolutely the best cheesecake I have EVER had. We drove down from Brooklyn and this food/wine/entertainment was out of this world. Couldn’t recommend them more! Even the house bread and olive oil was phenomenal!
Excellent food! Made me miss Italy! Great service!

Germano's is my favorite restaurant in Little Italy!! They have wonderful cabarets run by Cyd, who is the kindest lady I have ever met. They always give me delicious options. You must try the cheesecake!!!

Incredible food, service, and ambiance. Germano is so hilarious and helpful. He directed us towards the perfect dish and wine pairing... red beet ravioli with a super tuscan

Amazing Brussels sprouts! The gnocchi was delicious. No complaints.
The bar is nice but the restaurant is dated and the food was greasy and not quite good. I had a veal masala dish. The service and staff were all exceptional though.

Valentine’s Day Ruined – We made a reservation a week in advance for 7:45pm for Valentine’s Day. Upon early arrival (7:30pm), the host confirmed our name on the reservation list and immediately proceeded to sit us at the bar. We were confused and thought there was no formal dining area. Two couples arrived after us and were seated upstairs in what seemed to be one of the formal dining areas. We then talked to the host about our reservation made days ahead and he agreed to move us to the dining area. As we waited at the bar with no service, after 10 minutes of waiting he informed us that all the tables were full. We said it was fine and decided to leave the restaurant. At this point, the host tells us that he could find us a table. We said thank you and left the restaurant. They seemed unapologetic and gave no importance to us, the customers. Furthermore, every restaurant we checked on this very cold night in Little Italy was full due the special occasion. Luckily, we found a restaurant that was accepting walk-ins, but this experience definitely left a very sour feeling to our night. I would not recommend Germano's Piattini to anyone!
Very attentive and good food and drinks for a large private party... About 60 people. Nicely done.

Polenta appetizer was delicious, veal marsala was extremely tough and chewy but sauce and spinach was good, cheesecake was amazing.

Quite possibly the most unimaginative, bland Italian food I've ever had.  The staff was very pleasant and attentive but everything else was,,,,meh.  I'm surprised by the high ratings and maybe I'm jaded.  But if you ever have a chance to dine in NY, Chicago, Boston or Providence you'll know what I mean.
The best Italian restaurant in Baltimore. Maybe the best restaurant, full stop.
Great service. Manager makes certain all are taken care of without being loud.
Fabulous dinner,  great service.

This is one of our favorite spots in Little Italy. Everything is fresh and made to order and tastes great. They were even able to accommodate us last night when the restaurant we originally had a reservation for wanted us to wait over an hour to be seated. This is a nice, relaxed dining experience.

I thought this was a great meal. Dishes were tasty and service was good. Was pleased with all aspects including serving size. Had a variety of flatbread apps, the gnocchi in a cream sauce (which was delicious), ceasar salad, and veal marsala. The cheese cake for dessert was nice as well.

excellent!!!

Great food and extremely friendly staff. Took my parents here somewhat by chance; we were in front of it when we finally got tired of hoping someone else would make a decision on where to eat. I'm definitely happy with our luck that night. I'll definitely be returning.
Great food! Gluton free choices. Good people too! And great cabaret upstairs.
We sat at the bar and enjoyed a salami and cheese plate. Everything was exquisite!

I ate here with my wife last night and it was one of the best Italian restaurants I've ever been to. And I've been to Italy! I recommend to order a couple small plates each and share so you can try a taste of everything. A few dishes you need to try are the porchetta, the beet ravioli, the tartufo flatbread, and the cheesecake.
A great place for some authentic Italian food in little Italy of Baltimore. Reasonably priced and nice proportions as well.
Exceptional food, service, and fun. Visit the Cabaret for the best live music in Baltimore.

Found this gem in Little Italy after going to the movies and loved everything! Janet, our waitress, suggested the red beet ravioli and I couldn’t have been happier. It’s not a dish I normally would have tried but was glad I did. I finished the meal off with quite possibly the best cheesecake I’ve ever had! Service was top notch and the food was incredible. This place is great for a cozy date night but there are other rooms if you wanna bring a crew and try a bunch of small plates. I will be back.
Pretty good Italian restaurant

Food was delicious, and the waitress was very nice, but the owners (managers) were extremely rude. We went in for lunch and the waitress misunderstood my co-worker's order by giving him the "large" portion of lasagna instead of the "small" portion of lasagna (even though the menu just said lasagna!), which was about a $6 difference.  When we received the bill, my co-worker notified the waitress that he was overcharged, and that he only wanted to pay for what he had ordered. The waitress notified the owner, who immediately came over and said that the waitress assumed he wanted the "large" order because he was a "big" guy and that if he didn't want to pay for it he should stop eating his meal! We explained that the menu just says lasagna and that the waitress just assumed the size, rather then asking him. The owner said we were being unreasonable and that she has never had this problem over the last 30 years (which I find doubtful).  She finally agreed to charge my coworker the correct amount, but could still be heard muttering at us under her breath!  In summary, food was great, waitress was great, owners were extremely rude and inappropriate, and I will never go back!
Pretty good!
Small-ish menu, no kids menu, though service was good and white bean soup was amazing

My wife and I were visiting from Arizonia. Spent the day touring the Inner Harbor, when she had a striking brilliant idea to walk over to Little Italy for a late lunch/early dinner. Most restaurants closed by 3pm and opened again at 5pm. Germano's was the only lace opened it seemed. The place was empty. The owners were conducting business at the bar, but quickly welcomed us in. The ambiance was cozy and quiet. Our service was excellent. (We were the only people there). She was informative and friendly. We ordered the fried calamari for starters. It was scarfed down quickly. I order the shrimp scampi and my wife had the gnocchi. Both were top notch! The gnocchi was so light and fluffy. My pasta was homemade and not too rich. We struggled to finish our plates but saved room for dessert. The cheesecake is an absolute must have! With a few beers the meal (with tip) was around $100. Worth every penny! I would definitely recommend. We will be back again if ever in Baltimore.
DO NOT EAT HERE!! MICE POOP EVERYWHERE
Good, reasonably priced food with very friendly staff. A great place for lunch!

Great place for a group gathering.  We were the guests at a fraternal convention and this was one of our "outside" events.  It was a short walk from our hotel in the Inner Harbor.   We were served appetizers while the Chef demonstrated making pasta from scratch.  There wasn't the capability to make some for the entire group upstairs but they brought up plates from the main kitchen.  Our choice in red or white wine was served with a fantastic pasta in brown sage butter.  I would highly recommend this to anyone looking for a group event.
Fantastic food, excellent service, and great drinks. Downstairs is perfect for hanging out with friends and sharing food and cocktails.

One of the worse dates of my life 2 years ago introduced me to this restaurant and I strongly believe that's the only purpose I met this person!  I live 90 minutes south in Virginia but will drive there back and forth just so I can bring home their "Beet Ravioli"!!  This is the best Italian Restaurant in the DMV area by far.
Amazing, quality Italian coming. They make their own pasta in house, which makes even the more simpler dishes like gnocchi incredible.
Good Northern Italian food
Food was very good, servers were very fast to bring things and we're on top of everything thing we needed,  whether it was refills or dessert or the coffee it was all around an amazing experience
Good food, friendly service. I went for one of their music events, which was amazing.
Nice small area, good food, just a long wait to get in with no formal waiting area.
Very nice staff.
Delicious food, good wine and cozy atmosphere.
great food, authentic Italian
Yum.  Great service too!  Looking forward to next visit and music upstairs

This is one of our favorite spots in Little Italy. Everything is fresh and made to order and tastes great. They were even able to accommodate us last night when the restaurant we originally had a reservation for wanted us to wait over an hour to be seated. This is a nice, relaxed dining experience.
Bread is great, pasta is great, calamari was terrible, octopus was good, Brussel sprouts were good.
Great food and fantastic service. I eat here about once a week and have never had a bad experience.
The food tastes like it does in the old country. Brussel sprouts are superb. Come during a show upstairs in the cabaret...You won't leave hungry or disappointed!

Germano's is an old school, yet cute looking little Italian restaurant. Note that their dishes are on the smaller side.  I ordered the Gamberi e Fagioli, which is grilled shrimp on a bean salad. While the two grilled shrimp were great, the dish is not worth it if you don't like beans. I also had the Tagliatelle al Ragu. It is their house-made tagliatelle pasta with their special ragu sauce with beef. It was a simple pasta dish, but I still enjoyed it.  Service was great. The server and other staff were really attentive.

This restaurant is absolutely charming and intimate! The food (all of it) is delicious.  The pasta's are all made in the restaurant by the chef. The grilled food tastes smoky and extremely flavorful and light.  They are health conscience so, there are a wide variety of vegitarian, vegan and gluten free meals. Germano and his wife and two lovely daughters are frequently present and helping to be sure things run smoothly and all guests are leaving happy.  This place is a real gem in Little Italy. The desserts are amazing and made there as well. Bongo bongo is 3 puff pasteries filled with vanilla cream and topped with melted Belgian chocolate.  The sweetest thing I discovered is that Germano is extremely particular about making the expresso drinks the authentic Itialian way, with the finest quality ground espresso beans available. Germanos has the old country Itialian charm and family atmosphere that we all hope for when stepping into this historic neighborhood. There is an intimate little Caberet upstairs that features some of the most talented Musicians in the area preforming each weekend. I simply loved the whole experience. I highly recommend it to all.
Very fresh and good. A bit pricey
Fantastic service and food. Beet ravioli is delicious.
Nice Restaurant with authentic kitchen. Good food, but can't completely live up to their prices.
Absolutely delightful restaurant in little Italy.  They have a great, affordable lunch menu! They are super accommodating to vegetarians.  I loved the food,wine, service,  and atmosphere.

Am absolutely delightful meal - everything was delicious.  We split the beet ravioli (lovely!), a mushroom / truffle oil flatbread pizza (wonderful medley of flavor), and a cheese stuffed grilled pepper (outta this world).  Finished with a cheesecake that could be the best cheesecake We ever had!  Even the coffee was good!
Good Italian food, served "small plate". Waiter was very good and owner/manager made sure, several times, that we were being taken care of.

Germano's Piattini is the best! We experienced excellent service. We had lunch and dinner and it was so good!!!  They have an outstanding menu. Lots of options. The owners are really warm and accomodating. Great people! This is a gem in Little Italy, Downtown Baltimore!
DELICIOUS. I had the Penne al Salmon and it was absolutely amazing. My only complaint was that there was not enough of it.
Great service, the food was amazing, but it was a little pricer than I expected.

INCREDIBLE! This was the first time I've been since the new menu and the food was absolutely outstanding. They had great healthy options as well. I recommend ordering several things to share so you can try a taste of everything. My favorite simple starters are the grilled vegetables, beet salad, and sliced prosciutto, pecorino, & other selections from the charcuterie board. My friend got the red beet ravioli and it was out of this world. It's always special trying unique dishes. I ordered the grilled octopus which was perfectly tender and delectable. We also ordered the salmone, which was light and savory. At the end of our meal we had vanilla gelato with espresso and bongo bongo, cream filled profiteroles with chocolate drizzled on top. All in all, everything is 5 stars at Germano's, from the food to the waiters, to Germano Fabiani's hospitality himself.
Great
A delicious restaurant. I recommend the grilled octopus. So tasty and tender.

Germano's has everything you could ask for in an Italian restaurant. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, the staff is friendly and attentive, and the food is delicious and authentic. I am a frequent visitor of Germano's, and each time the food amazes me. The calamari, grilled or fried is wonderful, as well as the prosciutto-wrapped grilled peaches. Creative twists on Italian classics in a wonderful atmosphere with reasonable prices...what more could you ask for? :)

The new piattini menu is outstanding and the remodeling downstairs is amazing!  I love the Antipasti, octopus arugula salad, beet salad, meatballs, Shrimp dishes, and the Tuscan cheese.  They have some of my favorite beers on tap as well including St. Barnardus and beers from Union brewery.  They even had Old Rasputin Imperial Stout on tap at one point which is very rare.  I also recommend getting the red wine they have which is from Tuscany.

The new menu at Germano's Piattini will keep you coming back for more!  There are so many wonderful choices for each and every palate and dietary sensitivity, from customary dishes to an amazing variety of small plates.  The food is exceptionally fresh and everything is made to order with thoughtful attention to taste and presentation.  The knowledgeable wait staff is graciously accommodating.  It is very easy to see that the owners have committed their years of experience and tradition to providing a quality experience for each of their guests.  In addition to consistently updating the menu to meet the interests of their discerning diners, the restaurant itself has recently undergone a "renaissance."  There are multiple choices for your dining environment, depending on comfort and occasion.  Accommodations are available for a fun date, an intimate dinner or a large party celebration.  And if you want a truly memorable night out, enjoy a fabulous dinner and an evening of outstanding entertainment at Germano's Cabaret.  Here again, there are selections for everyone's tastes, so Google the calendar for the Cabaret, find the music that appeals to you and, by all means, call and make your reservations.  You will see why you will be ready to go back for more!

Outstanding! We had dinner last evening with a friend who recommended Germano's . What a treat! The lemon risotto with lobster was delizioso, the guys enjoyed Spaghetti Vongole. Dessert was 4 Profiteroles, a cream puffs filled with whipped cream, and drizzled with Belgium Chocolate. YUM! We haven't had them since we lived in Naples, Italy. We will be going back soon.

I can't say enough kind things about our experience here.    The pasta was made by hand minutes before we ordered.   The chef and owners welcomed us warmly.    I can't wait to get back to Baltimore to do it exactly the same way all over again.   Thanks Germano's for a wonderful evening.

My shrimp fra diavolo was one of the best I ever had. My wife's chicken parmesan, on the other hand, was very tough... Difficult to cut through even with a knife. Overall, we would come back and recommend to a friend.
Slow, expensive, unfriendly service. We get yelled at by the manager/owner after making us wait for 25 min after reserved a table in a half-empty restaurant!!! Do not come here!
